    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-03-05T07:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-03-05T07:00:00-05:00" n="33"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d33">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">762.63/170: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Geneva</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gilbert</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Geneva</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-03-05T13:00:00+01:00"
                            >March 5, 1934—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received March 6—12:30 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>38. Legation Vienna, No. 35, February 27, 1 p.m.<note n="18" xml:id="d33fn18">Not
                        printed.</note> The Austrian Government has not yet approached the League in
                    any way and there are no further indications of its intention to do so
                    (Consulate’s No. 30, February 16, 3 p.m.<note n="18" xml:id="d33fn19">Not
                        printed.</note>).</p>
                <p>The League official estimate is that Austria’s coming to Geneva becomes less
                    probable and that particularly in view of the present Italian position as
                    interpreted here Vienna in any event will not make any <hi rend="italic"
                        >démarche</hi> at Geneva until after the projected tripartite conversations
                    with Hungary and Italy.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gilbert</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
